<div class="truncated-body">



                <p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-33657" src="https://images.law.com/contrib/content/uploads/sites/390/2019/04/Cracked-security-Article-201904012132.jpg" alt="" width="620" height="372"></p>


                <p>There is a disconnect between rank-and-file employees and chief security officers on who is to blame in the event of a data breach, according to a report published last week by Egress Software Technologies Ltd. and Opinion Matters.</p>














